<div id="ta190_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>It consists on a <b>key word transformation</b> task in which the students have to show their knowledge of the lexical and lexico-grammatical of the English language.</p>
<p>Students will face an exercise in which they have to fill a gap in a sentence so that the meaning is the same as in a sentence provided before. In order to do it students have to use between two to five words one of which is provided.</p>
<p>Tips:</p>
<ul>
<li>Make sure that the answer has the same meaning as the original sentence.</li>
<li>Count the words: contractions count as two words.</li>
<li>Think about whether you need an expression, a phrasal verb and what grammar you need (change active to passive or put something into reported speech).</li>
</ul>
</div>
